    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2003-03-13</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2003-07-17T15:21:15Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>New Automobile Add-On Disclosure and Consumer Protection Act - Requires each dealer to disclose to each consumer that purchases a new automobile: (1) a dealer add-on invoice; and (2) a dealer add-on warranty statement.</p> <p>Specifies the timing of such disclosures.</p> <p>States that dealer violation of this Act results in liability to the United States for a civil penalty of not more than $10,000 or the total cost of the new automobile involved (including add-ons, taxes, and any other fees charged to the customer by the dealer), whichever is greater.</p> <p>Permits a private right of action by a consumer aggrieved by a violation of this Act.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
